description:
Recently sold: $545,900. 80 Acre Country Estate!  This stately home has been recently updated and shows like brand new!  Features;  Andersen double hung windows, granite countertops throughout, main floor master suite with amazing marble and glass master bathroom with a shower big enough for two and a claw foot tub for relaxing, white oak hardwood flooring throughout main level, granite top double islands in the kitchen with farm sink, updated lighting, new stainless steel appliances, new carpet upstairs, 450 square foot 3 season porch, 600 square foot covered front porch, an additional 2,000 square feet in basement awaits your finishing touch! Oversized three stall attached garage has off peak in-floor heat, and 96x48 out building is partially heated with office & bath.

You can have it all with this spectacular 80 acre country estate!  Don't sacrifice a thing!  Only 5 minutes from I-35 freeway access and stores/schools/restaurants in Pine City, 30 minutes to Forest Lake and 55 minutes to Downtown.  Entertain, relax, hunt, run a business, or run a farm. Truly an oasis providing privacy and security.  Closest neighbor is more than a quarter of a mile away.

Amazing value, quality construction, and a well thought out open floor plan!  Enjoy an abundance of built-ins and storage everywhere, from lockers and bench in the mud room, to wine rack and pantries in the kitchen, plus numerous oversized closets throughout!

The 96x48 pole building is a huge bonus!  Restore cars, have a cabinet shop, storage business, the possibilities are endless! This building features; 14 ft. ceiling height (perfect for hoist) and concrete floors.  One half of the out building is finished, plumbed and heated as a shop and office and the other half is cold storage. There are three, twelve foot wide overhead doors and two addition roller doors.

The land is roughly split between the front 40 acres of tillable/pasture and house site and the back 40 acres is woods/recreational land.  The property is zoned agricultural. No restrictions! It can be used to run horses or cattle or whatever you would like.

There is 3,600 feet of in-ground summer water lines to supply water to gardens, yard and pasture.  There is 28 acres that is tillable land that is used for hay and pasture and an additional 4 acres of dedicated pasture land.  Current owner has been raising grass fed beef using organic sustainable practices including permaculture.  Land features; mature oaks and timber with enough water and meadows to draw in the big deer.
